PROJECT SUMMARY

Project Title: Notepad Application Using Java Swing

University: Khushal Khan Khattak University, Karak (KKKUK)

Instructor: Dr. Arshad Iqbal

Developed By:

Naeem Ullah

Abdul Salam

Muhammad Afshan

Introduction:
The Notepad Application is a desktop-based text editor developed using Java Swing. It allows users to create, edit, and manage text documents efficiently.

Purpose of the Project:
The purpose of this project is to gain practical experience in Java GUI development and file handling. It also strengthens knowledge of event-driven programming and object-oriented concepts.

Scope of the Project:
This application can be used by students and professionals for writing and editing simple text documents.

Key Features:

New file creation

Open and save text files

Edit options (Cut, Copy, Paste)

Scrollable text area

Menu-driven interface

Tools and Technologies:

Java

Java Swing

AWT

File Handling

Event Handling

Conclusion:
The Notepad project successfully demonstrates how to build a functional desktop text editor using Java Swing. It improves programming skills and understanding of GUI and file management systems.
